      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sensitivity analysis must identify influential input parameters; nominal values must be traceable to measured or literature-sourced data.",
      "rationale": "One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis performed for rotational speed (±5%), inlet flow rate (±10%), and fluid viscosity (±15%). Rotational speed identified as most influential parameter for NIH. All nominal input values traceable to calibrated measurement records or published material property databases."
